                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-98-off515 t18281204-98-cd517"></join> last by banns, at St. Dunstan's, Stepney.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. He knew every thing concerning it - I had lived with him four or five months, and was in the family-<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182812040041"></xptr>way; I told him I was married; he said if I did not have him he would kill me; he said he would be a father to my child, and he would have me - and he went to my father to know what name I was to be married in; he dined there, and had beans and bacon for dinner. Witness. No; I never dined there in my life.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-98-person880">
                  WILLIAM 
                  EAGLES
